<Action id="55534" issue="26758" author="lehors" type="comment" created="2019-01-11 14:09:33.0" updateauthor="lehors" updated="2019-01-11 14:20:09.0"> <body><! CDATA A couple of observations on this: # some of these examples are extensively used for testing, chaincode/go/example02 in particular # at least one of them is merely used for testing: chaincode/go/example03 actually reads: // This program is an erroneous chaincode program that attempts to put state in query context - query should return error  So, I'm not sure we really want to move all of what's under fabric/examples to fabric-samples. Instead, I think we should only move the actual examples (this is still the majority), and keep what's used for testing within fabric under a different directory name like "test" or maybe the existing unit-test directory?  Thoughts?  ></body> </Action>
