<Action id="55580" issue="26758" author="muralisr" type="comment" created="2019-01-13 18:39:53.0" updateauthor="muralisr" updated="2019-01-13 18:39:53.0"> <body><! CDATA   ~lehors  Make sense not moving all examples to fabric-samples and renaming "examples" to "test-artifacts" or something.  This will also give us time to move true examples into samples (they'd need to be vetted and made complete with docs etc to be fit for fabric-samples).  ></body> </Action>
<Action id="55619" issue="26758" author="lehors" type="comment" created="2019-01-14 15:37:38.0" updateauthor="lehors" updated="2019-01-14 15:37:38.0"> <body><! CDATA Thanks for your input.  I wouldn't be quite that shy about it though. I think we should move every example that is not used for testing purposes within the fabric repo. I agree some examples would benefit from additional documentation but I don't see why that would be a prerequisite to the move. This can be done after the move just as well.     ></body> </Action>
